You are reviewing a Pull Request for the MyOrdersRewardProgram screen migration from Redux to Zustand.

## Context
This is a React Native microfrontend for Reward Program. The migration task requires:
1. NO Redux remnants (no connect(), no mapStateToProps, no bindActionCreators, no react-redux imports)
2. Proper Zustand integration (useRootStore with useShallow)
3. Hook Component pattern (index.tsx logic + view.tsx render)
4. Types properly imported from services/models
5. NO logic changes - only structure migration

## Files to Review

### models/index.ts
```typescript
import { PropsModalizeRef } from "@semparar/design-system-app/src/@types/modelize";
import { TypesTagLabel } from "@semparar/design-system-app/src/atomic/molecules/TagLabel/Models";
import { PointsTransaction } from "../../../services/models";

export const STATUS_COLORS: Record<string, TypesTagLabel> = {
    Pendente: 'highlight',
    Confirmado: 'highlight',
    Enviado: 'success',
    Finalizado: 'success',
    Estornado: 'error',
    Cancelado: 'alert'
};

export interface MyOrdersItem {
    id: string
    date: string
    description: string
    type: string
    amount: string
    icon: string
    status: string
    origination: string
}
export interface MyOrdersItemPropsView {
    myOrders: PointsTransaction[]
    emptyImage: string
    isLoading: boolean
    isError: boolean
    modalizeRefFilters: React.RefObject<PropsModalizeRef | null>
    filterGroups: {
        label: string;
        options: {
            label: string;
            value: number | string;
        }[];
    }[];
    isRefreshing: boolean;
    skeletonCount: number;
    screenWidth: number;
    formatDate: (iso?: string) => string;
    handleGoBack: () => void;
    handleOpenFilters: () => void;
    handleDetailsOrders: () => void;
    handleRefresh: () => void;
}
```

### view.tsx
```tsx
import React, { FC, RefObject } from "react"
